This is release 2.0.3 of the Jikes RVM. The main purposes
of this release are bug fixes, ???

Highlights include:
  -- Improved jdp on Linux/IA32. Previously several commands
     with BaseOpt or OptOpt type builds would crash with a message
     about "Pop wrong type" - that's now been fixed. 
  -- Other jdp improvements include: requiring hex values to
     be prefixed with '0x' or '0X'; clarifications in the help
     messages and userguide; stepline command fixed for BaseBase
     type builds; and print variable-name command fixed for BaseBase
     when LoadLocalVariableTable is true; However jdp still works
     better with BaseBase builds. 
  

